              Dr. Fatoki trained at Cook County Hospital and attended medical school at the University of Illinois. In addition to three board certifications, he also holds a Master's in Public Health from the University of Illinois, as well as a Master's in Addiction from Governor's State University.
                <br><br>
              In 2007, Dr. Fatoki began designing a unique, lifestyle modification program to target obesity and obesity-related disorders. The program works with the foods you already enjoy eating, which allows patients to avoid the weight loss and subsequent weight gain traditionally associated with diets and meal replacements. His program has been extrememly effective treating chronic illnesses such as high blood pressure, high cholesterol, diabetes, high triglycerides and sleep anea. In 2010 and 2011 he was recognized for leading a Veterans Affairs High Performing PACT Team, one of the only physicians to ever receive that designation in consecutive years. <br>
            </p>
                   
